h3cPsePortTable.name: h3cPsePortTable
h3cPsePortTable.description: The indexing scheme is taken form that used by the IETF Power MIB. The same indexing scheme is used to give continuity in behaviour between that standard and this extensions definitioin.

h3cPsePortEntry.name: h3cPsePortEntry
h3cPsePortEntry.description: The pethPsePortGroupIndex is imported from the IETF Power MIB and uniquely identifies the group containing the port to which power ethernet PSE is connected. Group means (box in the stack, module in a rack). The pethPsePortPowerIndex is imported from the IETF Power MIB and uniquely identifies the power ethernet PSE port within group pethPseGroupIndex to which the power Ethernet PSE entry is connected. This value will match the local port number on a switch.

h3cPsePortFaultDescription.name: h3cPsePortFaultDescription
h3cPsePortFaultDescription.description: The object supports the fault category of the IETF Power MIB [1] pethPsePortDetectionStatus object. A textual description containing more information about the nature of this fault is provided by this object. Typically this will detail the precise PoE hardware state which is causing the pethPsePortDetectionStatus object to be in the 'fault' state. It is a DisplayString of up to 255 characters.

h3cPsePortPeakPower.name: h3cPsePortPeakPower
h3cPsePortPeakPower.description: The object specifies the peak power which has been consumed by the port. It is defined as the highest measured value of power in milliWatts that has been consumed by the port. Its value is only reset when link is lost, the port is PoE disabled or when it is manually reset by the user asspecified below. It is a read/write integer value with units of milliWatts. Writing a value of zero to this object resets its value to zero. Writing any other value to this object has no effect on its value and an error is returned.

h3cPsePortAveragePower.name: h3cPsePortAveragePower
h3cPsePortAveragePower.description: The object specifies the average power which has been consumed by the port. This object is a read/write integer value with units of milliWatts. Writing a value of zero to this object resets its value to zero. Writing any other value to this object has no effect on its value and an error is returned.

h3cPsePortCurrentPower.name: h3cPsePortCurrentPower
h3cPsePortCurrentPower.description: The object specifies the power currently being consumed by the port. It is a read only integer value with units of milliWatts.

h3cPsePortPowerLimit.name: h3cPsePortPowerLimit
h3cPsePortPowerLimit.description: The object specifies the power limit set for this port. The PSE will not supply more than this level of power to the specified port. It is a read/write integer value with units of milliWatts.

h3cPsePortProfileIndex.name: h3cPsePortProfileIndex
h3cPsePortProfileIndex.description: Indicates the power profile which is currently associated with this port. This object references the corresponding h3cPseProfileIndex object in the power profiles table. A value of zero is a special case and indicates that no power profile is currently associated with this port. When h3cPseProfileIndex is set to an index of existent profile, pethPsePortPowerPairs, pethPsePortPowerPriority, pethPsePortAdminEnable and h3cPsePortPowerLimit will be set to the same as corresponding value. PethPsePortPowerPairs, pethPsePortPowerPriority and pethPsePortAdminEnable are objects of rfc3621-Power-Ethernet.mib.

h3cMainPseEntry.name: h3cMainPseEntry
h3cMainPseEntry.description: The pethMainPseGroupIndex is imported from the IETF Power MIB and uniquely identifies the group containing the port to which power ethernet PSE is connected. Group means (box in the stack, module in a rack) and the value 1 MUST be used for non-modular devices.

h3cMainPsePowerLimit.name: h3cMainPsePowerLimit
h3cMainPsePowerLimit.description: The object specifies the power limit set for the unit as a whole. The PoE unit will already have a nominal power defined by the IETF Power MIB [1] pethMainPsePower object. This OPTIONAL object specifies a further limit to this nominal power value. This may be useful to control the thermals of the unit, or for internal testing purposes. One possible use for this object may be to lower the power consumption of the unit if one or more of the internal fans have broken. It is a read/write integer value with units of Watts (note - Watts is chosen instead of milliWatts here since the IETF Power MIB [1] measures unit based parameters, such as the pethMainPsePower object, in units of Watts).

h3cMainPseAveragePower.name: h3cMainPseAveragePower
h3cMainPseAveragePower.description: The object specifies the average power which has been consumed by the port. It is a read/write integer value with units of Watts (note - Watts is chosen instead of milliWatts here since the IETF Power MIB [1] measures unit based parameters, such as the pethMainPsePower object, in units of Watts). Writing a value of zero to this object resets its value to zero. Writing any other value to this object has no effect on its value and an error is returned.

h3cMainPsePeakPower.name: h3cMainPsePeakPower
h3cMainPsePeakPower.description: The object specifies the peak power which has been consumed for PoE. It is defined as the highest measured value of power in milliWatts that has been consumed at any one point in time by the sum of the PoE ports. Its value is only reset when the unit is powered on or when it is manually reset by the user as specifiedbelow. It is a read/write integer value with units of Watts (note - Watts is chosen instead of milliWatts here since the IETF Power MIB [1] measures unit based parameters, such as the pethMainPsePower object, in units of Watts). Writing a value of zero to this object resets its value to zero. Writing any other value to this object has noeffect on its value and an error is returned.

h3cMainGuaranteedPowerRemaining.name: h3cMainGuaranteedPowerRemaining
h3cMainGuaranteedPowerRemaining.description: The object specifies the amount of power remaining in the guaranteed power pool. Each time a port is placed into guaranteed mode it reserves a set amount of power out of the total guaranteed power pool for the system. This intention of this object is to give the client of this MIB (whether that be the CLI or the Web interface or the end user) an indication of how many ports can still be placed into guaranteed mode. It is a read only integer value with units of Watts(note - Watts is chosen instead of milliWatts here since the IETF Power MIB [1] measures unit based parameters,such as the pethMainPsePower object, in units of Watts).

h3cMainPsePriorityMode.name: h3cMainPsePriorityMode
h3cMainPsePriorityMode.description: Describes or controls the priority mode on slot which must be enabled firstly. When a new board is inserted, and the power is over-load, a value of disconnection(0) means that the power will stop supply to the low priority slot ; A value of non-disconnection(1) means that the slot still supply when a new board is inserted, and the power is over-load too.

h3cMainPseLegacy.name: h3cMainPseLegacy
h3cMainPseLegacy.description: Describes or controls the legacy mode on slot which must be enabled firstly. Legacy mode: standard or nonstandard PD detection mode.

h3cMainPsePowerPriority.name: h3cMainPsePowerPriority
h3cMainPsePowerPriority.description: Describes or controls the priority of the PSE. The priority will be used by the PSE policy to prevent from power overloading. If the priority of PSE is set to critical, the PSE will turn into guaranteed mode. The priority could be used by a control mechanism that prevents power overloading by disconnecting PSEs with lower power priority. PSEs that connect devices critical to the application should be set to higher priority.

h3cPseProfilesTable.name: h3cPseProfilesTable
h3cPseProfilesTable.description: A table of objects representing a set of power profiles. Power profiles can be applied to PoE ports, which have the effect of automatically setting the priority, power limit and PoE enable MIB objects to the values specified in the power profile.

h3cPseProfilesEntry.name: h3cPseProfilesEntry
h3cPseProfilesEntry.description: A set of objects that display and control the Main power of a PSE.

h3cPseProfileIndex.name: h3cPseProfileIndex
h3cPseProfileIndex.description: The index of the profile. This uniquely allow the profile to be identified.

h3cPseProfileName.name: h3cPseProfileName
h3cPseProfileName.description: Assigns the profile a name with which the settings can be assiciated with. For example, 'NBX Phone'.

h3cPseProfilePowerMode.name: h3cPseProfilePowerMode
h3cPseProfilePowerMode.description: The power mode associated with this power profile. There are two possible power modes as follows: powerDisabled, powerEnabled. When a power profile is applied to a PSE port, this value dictates the settings of the ports pethPsePortPowerPriority and pethPsePortAdminEnable objects.

h3cPseProfilePowerLimit.name: h3cPseProfilePowerLimit
h3cPseProfilePowerLimit.description: The power limit to be applied to the ports h3cPsePortPowerLimit object when the profile is applied to the PSE port. Expressed in milliWatts.

h3cPseProfilePriority.name: h3cPseProfilePriority
h3cPseProfilePriority.description: This object controls the priority of the port from the point of view of a power management algorithm. The priority that is set by this variable could be used by a control mechanism that prevents over current situations by disconnecting first ports with lower power priority. Ports that connect devices critical to the operation of the network - like the E911 telephones ports - should be set to higher priority.

h3cPseProfilePairs.name: h3cPseProfilePairs
h3cPseProfilePairs.description: Describes or controls the pairs in use. If the value of pethPsePortPowerPairsControl is true, this object is writable. A value of signal(1) means that the signal pairs only are in use. A value of spare(2) means that the spare pairs only are in use.

h3cPseProfileApplyNum.name: h3cPseProfileApplyNum
h3cPseProfileApplyNum.description: The number of this profile which has been applied. If h3cPseProfileApplyNum is not zero, user can't change the current line.

h3cPseProfileRowStatus.name: h3cPseProfileRowStatus
h3cPseProfileRowStatus.description: The status of this classifier. If h3cPseProfileApplyNum is not zero, user can't delete the current line.

h3cPseAutoDetectActive.name: h3cPseAutoDetectActive
h3cPseAutoDetectActive.description: The object specifies whether the device auto-detection feature is active. If this object is set to Active, and a known powered device is detected, then the port will automatically switch to Auto-Guaranteed mode. This is a stackwide object (ie. it is not referenced by group index).

h3cPsePowerMaxValue.name: h3cPsePowerMaxValue
h3cPsePowerMaxValue.description: The object specifies the max poe power for lanswitch. The value should between the power currently and the max power.

h3cPsePolicyMode.name: h3cPsePolicyMode
h3cPsePolicyMode.description: The PSE policy only applies to the situation that when a new board (PSE) is inserted, and the power is overload. A value of priority(2) means that the power will stop supplying to the low priority PSE. About PSE priority, please refer to h3cMainPsePowerPriority. A value of disabled(1) means that the power will stop supplying to the new inserted PSE. The default value of this object is disabled(1).

h3cPDPolicyMode.name: h3cPDPolicyMode
h3cPDPolicyMode.description: The PD policy only applies to the situation that when a new PD is inserted, and the power of PSE is overload. A value of priority(2) means that the power will stop supplying to the low priority port PD. About port priority, please refer to pethPsePortPowerPriority. A value of disabled(1) means that the slot stop supplying to the new inserted PD. The default value of this object is disabled(1).

h3cpsePDChangeNotification.name: h3cpsePDChangeNotification
h3cpsePDChangeNotification.description: This notification indicates if PD has been inserted or pulled out.

h3cPOEDisconnectNotification.name: h3cPOEDisconnectNotification
h3cPOEDisconnectNotification.description: This notification indicates the POE power module does not disconnect.

h3cPOEInputErrorNotification.name: h3cPOEInputErrorNotification
h3cPOEInputErrorNotification.description: This notification indicates the POE power module input error.

h3cPOEOutputErrorNotification.name: h3cPOEOutputErrorNotification
h3cPOEOutputErrorNotification.description: This notification indicates the POE power module output error.

h3cPOEOverVoltageNotification.name: h3cPOEOverVoltageNotification
h3cPOEOverVoltageNotification.description: This notification indicates the POE power module overruns the voltage limit.

h3cPOEOverTempNotification.name: h3cPOEOverTempNotification
h3cPOEOverTempNotification.description: This notification indicates the POE power module overruns the temperature limit.

h3cPOEFanErrorNotification.name: h3cPOEFanErrorNotification
h3cPOEFanErrorNotification.description: This notification indicates the POE power module fan error.

h3cPOEModuleShutdownNotification.name: h3cPOEModuleShutdownNotification
h3cPOEModuleShutdownNotification.description: This notification indicates the POE power module is closed.

h3cPOECurRestrictedNotification.name: h3cPOECurRestrictedNotification
h3cPOECurRestrictedNotification.description: This notification indicates the POE power module current is restricted.

h3cPOEACSwitchNotification.name: h3cPOEACSwitchNotification
h3cPOEACSwitchNotification.description: This notification indicates the AC input switch alarm of this POE power.

h3cPOEACInCurANotification.name: h3cPOEACInCurANotification
h3cPOEACInCurANotification.description: This notification indicates the AC input current A alarm state of this POE power.

h3cPOEACInCurBNotification.name: h3cPOEACInCurBNotification
h3cPOEACInCurBNotification.description: This notification indicates the AC input current B alarm state of this POE power.

h3cPOEACInCurCNotification.name: h3cPOEACInCurCNotification
h3cPOEACInCurCNotification.description: This notification indicates the AC input current C alarm state of this POE power.

h3cPOEACSwitchVolABNotification.name: h3cPOEACSwitchVolABNotification
h3cPOEACSwitchVolABNotification.description: This notification indicates the AC input voltage AB alarm state of this POE power.

h3cPOEACSwitchVolBCNotification.name: h3cPOEACSwitchVolBCNotification
h3cPOEACSwitchVolBCNotification.description: This notification indicates the AC input voltage BC alarm state of this POE power.

h3cPOEACSwitchVolCANotification.name: h3cPOEACSwitchVolCANotification
h3cPOEACSwitchVolCANotification.description: This notification indicates the AC input voltage CA alarm state of this POE power.

h3cPOEDCOutVolNotification.name: h3cPOEDCOutVolNotification
h3cPOEDCOutVolNotification.description: This notification indicates the DC output alarm of this POE power.

h3cPOEShutdownNotification.name: h3cPOEShutdownNotification
h3cPOEShutdownNotification.description: This notification indicates the whole POE power has been shutdown.

h3cPsePortGroup.name: h3cPsePortGroup
h3cPsePortGroup.description: A collection of objects should be supported at the same time.

h3cMainPseGroup.name: h3cMainPseGroup
h3cMainPseGroup.description: A collection of objects should be supported at the same time.

h3cPseScalarGroup.name: h3cPseScalarGroup
h3cPseScalarGroup.description: A collection of scalar objects supported.

h3cPseProfilesGroup.name: h3cPseProfilesGroup
h3cPseProfilesGroup.description: A collection of objects should be supported at the same time.

h3cPOEPowerDCOutStateGroup.name: h3cPOEPowerDCOutStateGroup
h3cPOEPowerDCOutStateGroup.description: The DC out power state group.

h3cPOEPowerDCOutInfoGroup.name: h3cPOEPowerDCOutInfoGroup
h3cPOEPowerDCOutInfoGroup.description: The power AC input switch information group

h3cPOEThresholdACMimimum.name: h3cPOEThresholdACMimimum
h3cPOEThresholdACMimimum.description: Input threshold AC minimum. It is a read-write node. The value of this node is 'OCTET STRING', it is used to describe a float value. So this string should fit the following rule: 1. This string should be terminated by '\0'; 2. Every characters should be number or radix point; 3. The radix point should occur only once, and it should not be the first or the last character of the string. The value of this node should be smaller than 264.0V and larger than 90.0V. And it should be smaller than the h3cPOEThresholdACMaximum.

h3cPOEThresholdACMaximum.name: h3cPOEThresholdACMaximum
h3cPOEThresholdACMaximum.description: Input threshold AC maximum. It is a read-write node. The value of this node is 'OCTET STRING', it is used to describe a float value. So this string should fit the following rule: 1. This string should be terminated by '\0'; 2. Every characters should be number or radix point; 3. The radix point should occur only once, and it should not be the first or the last character of the string. It should be smaller than 264.0V and larger than 90.0V. And it should be larger than the h3cPOEThresholdACMinimum.

h3cPOEThresholdDCMinimum.name: h3cPOEThresholdDCMinimum
h3cPOEThresholdDCMinimum.description: Input threshold DC minimum. It is a read-write node. The value of this node is 'OCTET STRING', it is used to describe a float value. So this string should fit the following rule: 1. This string should be terminated by '\0'; 2. Every characters should be number or radix point; 3. The radix point should occur only once, and it should not be the first or the last character of the string. It should be smaller than 47.0V and larger than 45.0V.

h3cPOEThresholdDCMaximum.name: h3cPOEThresholdDCMaximum
h3cPOEThresholdDCMaximum.description: Input threshold DC maximum. It is a read-write node. The value of this node is 'OCTET STRING', it is used to describe a float value. So this string should fit the following rule: 1. This string should be terminated by '\0'; 2. Every characters should be number or radix point; 3. The radix point should occur only once, and it should not be the first or the last character of the string. It should be smaller than 57.0V and larger than 55.0V.

h3cPOEPowerModuleNum.name: h3cPOEPowerModuleNum
h3cPOEPowerModuleNum.description: The number of the power modules.

h3cPOESupervisionModuleName.name: h3cPOESupervisionModuleName
h3cPOESupervisionModuleName.description: The object specifies the Supervision Module name on this POE power.

h3cPOESMMajorVersion.name: h3cPOESMMajorVersion
h3cPOESMMajorVersion.description: The object specifies the high byte of the monitor module version.

h3cPOESMMinorVersion.name: h3cPOESMMinorVersion
h3cPOESMMinorVersion.description: The object specifies the low byte of the monitor module version.

h3cPOESMFactorName.name: h3cPOESMFactorName
h3cPOESMFactorName.description: The object specifies the name of the manufactor.

h3cPOEModuleInfoTable.name: h3cPOEModuleInfoTable
h3cPOEModuleInfoTable.description: The table of the module information on this POE power.

h3cPOEModuleInfoEntry.name: h3cPOEModuleInfoEntry
h3cPOEModuleInfoEntry.description: The entry of the module information on this POE power.

h3cPOEModuleIndex.name: h3cPOEModuleIndex
h3cPOEModuleIndex.description: The index of the current module on this POE power. It is also the index of h3cPOEModuleInfoTable. The range of this node is from 1 to h3cPOEPowerModuleNum.

h3cPOEModuleID.name: h3cPOEModuleID
h3cPOEModuleID.description: The ID of the current module on this POE power.

h3cPOEModuleInfoPower.name: h3cPOEModuleInfoPower
h3cPOEModuleInfoPower.description: The power of the current module on this POE power.

h3cPOEModuleHardVerInfo.name: h3cPOEModuleHardVerInfo
h3cPOEModuleHardVerInfo.description: The hardware version information of the current module on this POE power.

h3cPOEDCOutStateModuleNum.name: h3cPOEDCOutStateModuleNum
h3cPOEDCOutStateModuleNum.description: The module number on this POE power. It is the maximum of the h3cPOEDCOutStateIndex.

h3cPOEDCOutStateTable.name: h3cPOEDCOutStateTable
h3cPOEDCOutStateTable.description: The table of DC output power state on this POE power.

h3cPOEDCOutStateEntry.name: h3cPOEDCOutStateEntry
h3cPOEDCOutStateEntry.description: The entry of the DC output power state on this POE power.

h3cPOEDCOutStateIndex.name: h3cPOEDCOutStateIndex
h3cPOEDCOutStateIndex.description: The index of the DC output power state on this POE power. The range of this node is from 1 to h3cPOEDCOutStateModuleNum.

h3cPOEDCOutDCVolAlarm.name: h3cPOEDCOutDCVolAlarm
h3cPOEDCOutDCVolAlarm.description: The DC output alarm of the DC output power state on this POE power. The value of this node will be the following values: normal (1), underLimit (2), aboveLimit (3), fuseBroken (4), switchOff (5), otherError (6).

h3cPOEDCOutCurNum.name: h3cPOEDCOutCurNum
h3cPOEDCOutCurNum.description: The number of DC output current on this POE power. It is the maximum of h3cPOEDCOutInfoIndex.

h3cPOEDCOutInfoTable.name: h3cPOEDCOutInfoTable
h3cPOEDCOutInfoTable.description: The table of the DC output information on this POE power.

h3cPOEDCOutInfoEntry.name: h3cPOEDCOutInfoEntry
h3cPOEDCOutInfoEntry.description: The entry of the DC output information on this POE power.

h3cPOEDCOutInfoIndex.name: h3cPOEDCOutInfoIndex
h3cPOEDCOutInfoIndex.description: The index of the DC output information on this POE POWER. The range of this node is from 1 to h3cPOEDCOutCurNum.

h3cPOEDCOutVol.name: h3cPOEDCOutVol
h3cPOEDCOutVol.description: The DC output voltage of the current DC output on this POE power.

h3cPOEDCOutInfoLoadCur.name: h3cPOEDCOutInfoLoadCur
h3cPOEDCOutInfoLoadCur.description: The total load current of the current DC output on this POE power.

h3cPOEACSwitchStateModuleNum.name: h3cPOEACSwitchStateModuleNum
h3cPOEACSwitchStateModuleNum.description: The number of the AC swtich state module on this POE power. It is the maximum of h3cPOEACSwitchStateIndex.

h3cPOEACSwitchStateTable.name: h3cPOEACSwitchStateTable
h3cPOEACSwitchStateTable.description: The table of the AC switch state on this POE power.

h3cPOEACSwitchStateEntry.name: h3cPOEACSwitchStateEntry
h3cPOEACSwitchStateEntry.description: The entry of the AC switch state on this POE power.

h3cPOEACSwitchStateIndex.name: h3cPOEACSwitchStateIndex
h3cPOEACSwitchStateIndex.description: The index of the AC switch state on this POE power. The range of this node is from 1 to h3cPOEACSwitchStateModuleNum.

h3cPOEACSwitchState.name: h3cPOEACSwitchState
h3cPOEACSwitchState.description: The AC switch state on this POE power. The value of this node will be one of the following values: on (1), off (2), highVoltInput (3), lowVoltInput (4)

h3cPOEInCurStateModuleNum.name: h3cPOEInCurStateModuleNum
h3cPOEInCurStateModuleNum.description: The DC input current state of the module on this POE power. It is the maximum of the h3cPOESwitchStateVolExIndex.

h3cPOEInCurAState.name: h3cPOEInCurAState
h3cPOEInCurAState.description: The current A state in the DC input on this POE power. normal (1), underLimit (2), aboveLimit (3), lackPhrase (4), fuseBroken (5), switchOff (6), otherError (7).

h3cPOEInCurBState.name: h3cPOEInCurBState
h3cPOEInCurBState.description: The current B state in the DC input on this POE power. The value of this node will be one of the following values: normal (1), underLimit (2), aboveLimit (3), lackPhrase (4), fuseBroken (5), switchOff (6), otherError (7).

h3cPOEInCurCState.name: h3cPOEInCurCState
h3cPOEInCurCState.description: The current C state in the DC input on this POE power. The value of this node will be one of the following values: normal (1), underLimit (2), aboveLimit (3), lackPhrase (4), fuseBroken (5), switchOff (6), otherError (7).

h3cPOESwitchStateVolExTable.name: h3cPOESwitchStateVolExTable
h3cPOESwitchStateVolExTable.description: All alarm status of the VOL status. The value of this node will be one of the following values: normal (1), underLimit (2), aboveLimit (3), lackPhrase (4), fuseBroken (5), switchOff (6), otherError (7).

h3cPOESwitchStateVolExEntry.name: h3cPOESwitchStateVolExEntry
h3cPOESwitchStateVolExEntry.description: The h3cPOESwitchStateVolExIndex will match the number of the VOL status.

h3cPOESwitchStateVolExIndex.name: h3cPOESwitchStateVolExIndex
h3cPOESwitchStateVolExIndex.description: The object species the index of the VOL status. The range of this node is from 1 to h3cPOEInCurStateModuleNum.

h3cPOESwitchStateInVolAB.name: h3cPOESwitchStateInVolAB
h3cPOESwitchStateInVolAB.description: The object specifies the VOL AB alarm in each VOL status. The value of this node will be one of the following values: normal (1), underLimit (2), aboveLimit (3), lackPhrase (4), fuseBroken (5), switchOff (6), otherError (7).

h3cPOESwitchStateInVolBC.name: h3cPOESwitchStateInVolBC
h3cPOESwitchStateInVolBC.description: The object specifies the VOL BC alarm in each VOL status. The value of this node will be one of the following values: normal (1), underLimit (2), aboveLimit (3), lackPhrase (4), fuseBroken (5), switchOff (6), otherError (7).

h3cPOESwitchStateInVolCA.name: h3cPOESwitchStateInVolCA
h3cPOESwitchStateInVolCA.description: The object specifies the VOL CA alarm in each VOL status. The value of this node will be one of the following values: normal (1), underLimit (2), aboveLimit (3), lackPhrase (4), fuseBroken (5), switchOff (6), otherError (7).

h3cPOEAlarmStateModuleNum.name: h3cPOEAlarmStateModuleNum
h3cPOEAlarmStateModuleNum.description: The object specifies the number of the power modules in alarm state.

h3cPOEAlarmStateInfoTable.name: h3cPOEAlarmStateInfoTable
h3cPOEAlarmStateInfoTable.description: All alarm states in the POE power modules.

h3cPOEAlarmStateInfoEntry.name: h3cPOEAlarmStateInfoEntry
h3cPOEAlarmStateInfoEntry.description: The h3cPOEAlarmModuleInfoIndex will match the number of the power module.

h3cPOEAlarmModuleInfoIndex.name: h3cPOEAlarmModuleInfoIndex
h3cPOEAlarmModuleInfoIndex.description: The index specifies the index of the H3cPOEAlarmStateInfoEntry table. The range of this node is from 1 to h3cPOEAlarmStateModuleNum.

h3cPOEModuleDisconnect.name: h3cPOEModuleDisconnect
h3cPOEModuleDisconnect.description: The node specifies the alarm state: The module does not link. The value of this node is one of the following values: normal (1), alarm (2).

h3cPOEModuleInputError.name: h3cPOEModuleInputError
h3cPOEModuleInputError.description: The node specifies the alarm state: Input error. The value of this node is one of the following values: normal (1), alarm (2).

h3cPOEModuleOutputError.name: h3cPOEModuleOutputError
h3cPOEModuleOutputError.description: The node specifies the alarm state: Output error. The value of this node is one of the following values: normal (1), alarm (2).

h3cPOEModuleOverVoltage.name: h3cPOEModuleOverVoltage
h3cPOEModuleOverVoltage.description: The node specifies the alarm state: The voltage is too high. The value of this node is one of the following values: normal (1), alarm (2).

h3cPOEModuleOverTemp.name: h3cPOEModuleOverTemp
h3cPOEModuleOverTemp.description: The node specifies the alarm state: The temperature is too high. The value of this node is one of the following values: normal (1), alarm (2).

h3cPOEModuleFanError.name: h3cPOEModuleFanError
